Summary: A photo spread on Facebook of a man walking over a mountain of corpses, saying it was a result of the government euthanizing elderly people to contain the virus - the photo is actually from the Walking Dead

Title: ¿Qué sabemos sobre la autoría del audio que habla del confinamiento y que se atribuye al magistrado de Tarragona Ángel Martínez Sáez? Él asegura que no es suyo
Narrative_Description: An audio message was spread saying it was by the magistrate Ángel Martínez Sáez and claiming the police cannot fine people for going out on the street
Motive_Description: Effort to discredit the magistrate Ángel Martínez Sáez by attributing an audio message to him
Key_Words: Coronavirus, magistrado, policìa, Ángel Martínez Sáez
Summary: An audio message was spread saying it was by the magistrate Ángel Martínez Sáez and claiming the police cannot fine people if they go out on the street. However, there is no proof that the recording was by the magistrate

Title: FALSE: Photo of Duterte doing the rounds during coronavirus pandemic
Narrative_Description: Reused photo from 2017 of Duterte in full gear claiming despite his old age and health he was still making rounds to keep Filipinos safe amidst the COVID pandemic
Motive_Description: Attempts to bolster Duterte's status, by claiming he was making rounds to make sure Filipinos are safe
Summary: Facebook post with photo of Duterte from 2017 in full army gear, claiming he was still making rounds to ensure the safety of Filipinos

Title: FALSE: Bills for March and April 2020 now free – Meralco
Narrative_Description: Video appearing to be a "breaking news" headline claiming the Philippine utilities company, Meralco, was waiving all bills for March and April
Motive_Description: The post appears to be "breaking news" with no particular intent but to provide "useful information"
Summary: Facebook post of a video appearing to be "breaking news" claiming Meralco, a Philippine utilities company, was waiving all fees for March and April

Title: Non, le roquefort n’est pas « un remède contre le Covid-19 »
Narrative_Description: Rumors that the mushroom used for the preparation of roquefort cheese can be used to cure the virus, and that it has been used by French doctor Didier Raoult
Motive_Description: Have people talk about Roquefort and stimulate the economy of the region where it is produced (as the author himself admitted)
Source_Description: Gregory Covinhes, a man from the Aveyron region
Key_Words: Coronavirus, roquefort, mushroom, cure, DIdier Raoult
Summary: The news spread that French Didier Raoult had succesfully used the mushroom at the base of the preparation of roquefort cheese as a cure for coronavirus, which was denied

Title: No, no es un político español fichando por otros en el Congreso por las dietas: es Ucrania
Narrative_Description: A video showing an MP voting in the Parliament with an ID and claiming this new identification method has been implemented because of the Covid-19 crisis
Motive_Description: Effort to attack the political class in general by saying they imposed a wrong security measure to vote in the Parliament
Summary: A video was shared on social media showing an MP using an ID to vote in the Parliament and accusing politicians to have implemented a wrong security policy to fight the crisis. However, the video, while real, refers to the Ukraine Parliament

Title: No, el producto ‘Covid-19 IgM/IgG’ no es una vacuna ni cura el coronavirus: es un test que detecta si el cuerpo está produciendo anticuerpos para luchar contra el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: A message saying that Covid-19 IgM/IgG is a vaccine against the virus and that Trump said Roche is going to launch the product next Sunday
Motive_Description: Effort to claim that a vaccine has been found by Roche and that it is going to be launched soon
Summary: A message was spread saying that Covid-19 IgM/IgG is a vaccine and that Trump said it will be launched soon by Roche. However, this is not a vaccine but rather a test to see whether the body is developing anti-corps to fight against the virus

Title: FALSE: P57 billion 'balance' in DSWD subsidy even if all families get coronavirus cash aid
Narrative_Description: Facebook post claiming the "math doesn't add up" on an emergency response the Philippine government was distributing, saying there was still more to spare
Motive_Description: Claiming that the Department of Social Welfare and Development in the Philippines is not using its resources properly, to undermine them
Summary: Facebook post claiming the math doesn't add up with a COVID-relief fund from the Department of Social Welfare and Development in the Philippines

Title: ¿Qué sabemos de la cadena que asegura que en Leganés (Madrid) entregan mascarillas impregnadas en cloroformo para robar en plena crisis del coronavirus? Policía Local y Policía Nacional no tienen constancia de ningún caso a 23 de abril
Narrative_Description: A message saying that in Leganes, in Madrid, there are people who sell masks full of chloroform at people's houses to then steal everything
Motive_Description: Spread a story saying there are thieves in Leganes to spark fear among citizens
Summary: A message was spread on WhatsApp saying that people were going to people's houses in Leganes, Madrid, to sell masks full of chloroform to then steal in people's houses. However, the Police said there is no evidence that this is true

Title: No, este anciano no está ingresado en La Paz ni en el Doctor Negrín ni en España por el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: A photo of an old man alone in a hospital was spread saying that he was left alone in the hospital during the covid-19 emergency and doesn't remember who he is
Motive_Description: Sprea a story saying that an old patient was left alone to spread fear among people
Summary: A photo of an old patient was spread saying that the man was left alone in a hospital due to the covid-19 emergency and saying he doesn't remember who he is. However, the photo was taken in 2017 and the man was in the en el Hospital Civil de Guadalajara en México

Title: Coronavirus : des bactéries intestinales, les « Prevotella », sont-elles les véritables responsables du Covid-19 ?
Narrative_Description: Claims that coronavirus acts on some intestinal bacteria and that therefore a cure should be easy to found
Motive_Description: Discredit the media and pharmaceutical companies by claiming they are hiding the information for their own profit
Summary: Messages were spread claiming research has established that coronavirus acts on the organism through some intestinal bacteria, which is false, that the cure could therefore be easy to find, and containing other misleading info, while attributing the information to a group of French doctors who denied the claim.

Title: Non, l’attestation de déplacement actuelle n’est pas un « copié-collé de celle de 1940 »
Narrative_Description: Claims that the self-declaration form used in France to go out during the emergency is a copy of the one used during the German occupation in WWII
Motive_Description: Discredit the government through a photomontage showing that it has copied the self-declaration form from the one Germany required during its occupation of France in WWII
Key_Words: Coronavirus, self-declaration form, emergency, France, Germany, occupation
Summary: A photomontage showed a self-declaration form to go out attributed to the German occupation of WWII and it came with claims that the government had copied it to create the current form for the coronavirus emergency

Title: El bulo del coronavirus y el desinfectante Lysol
Narrative_Description: A message spread saying that this coronavirus is not different from the ones discovered in the past since Lysol, a disinfectant, is effective against this virus as it is with past viruses and that panick has been created to sell some drugs or hide some things
Motive_Description: Effort to say that this coronavirus is not different from the ones already discovered, minimizing the effects of the virus
Summary: A message was spread saying that the virus is not different from past coronaviruses and that panick was created to hide some things or to sell some medical drugs. The proof of this would be that Lysol, a disinfectant, is able to protect against Covid-19 as with other coronaviruses. However, this is not true since Covid-19 is a new completely different virus.

Title: No, el Gobierno no se ha equivocado e ingresado 3000 euros en unas "tarjetas solidarias" para "familias gitanas": el autor del vídeo ha reconocido que se lo inventó
Narrative_Description: A video in which a man said that the Spanish government gave 3,000 euros to all Gypsy families through a "solidarity card"
Motive_Description: Effort to attack the current politicians and to spread an anti-Gypsy rhetoric
Summary: A video was spread in which a man said that the Spanish government allocated 3,000 euros to each Gypsy family through "solidarity cards". However, this is not true.

Title: ¿Qué sabemos sobre los respiradores que el Gobierno de Castilla-La Mancha compró a una empresa turca?
Narrative_Description: A message was spreas saying that the government of Castilla-La Mancha bought 100 respirators from a Turkish company which designed them in 1984, and that is why they are obsolete
Motive_Description: Effort to discredit the Castilla-La Mancha administration to spread distrust toward institutions
Key_Words: Coronavirus, respiratores, Castilla-La Mancha, empresa turca
Summary: A message was spread saying that the government of Castilla-La Mancha bought 100 respirators from a Turkish company which designed them in 1984, and thus they cannot be used since they are obsolete. However, the company designed them in 2001 and they work perfectly.

Title: No, la foto de musulmanes rezando en grupo en azoteas que se mueve como si fuera durante el confinamiento por coronavirus no es en España: es en Dubai
Narrative_Description: A photo showing Muslims grouped in various places and saying that the Spanish government has suspended all Catholic celebrations and doesn't do anythin about Muslim ones.
Motive_Description: Effort to criticize current politicians and push an anti-Muslim rhetoric
Summary: A photo showing Muslims grouped in different places was spread claiming that the Spanish government has suspended all Catholic celebrations but doesn't do anything about this. However, the photo was taken in Dubai, not in Spain
